data.title: A suggestion to Erich Gamma
data.body:
Allow me state a very strong support for the improvement suggestion by Rob Eisenberg (of the **[Aurelia](http://aurelia.io/) fame**) written [here](https://visualstudio.uservoice.com/forums/293070-visual-studio-code/suggestions/13877736-better-support-for-esnext) and repeate below. for reader's convencience:

> VSCode currently does a decent job of supporting ES2015. However, the language is moving fast and technologies like Babel allow us to use future features faster.
> 
> In general, VSCode needs better support for ESNext. This includes a host of features such as class instance fields, decorators, async/await, exponentiation and more. It would be nice if the underlying engine could enable selecting which features were desired and enable the VSCode team to easily and quickly extend supported language features in the future. Regardless, it would be nice if the editor, at least, did not generate red squiggly error messages every time I used a language feature it didn't understand.

data.title: fix #5918
data.body:
**Problem**: Intellisense provider is adding '**,**' for the selection in a special case when intellisense was triggered for the quoted property when it is the last one and the cursor is before the end quote. 

This is because, we ask parse the rest of the string to see if the next token is a completion token for json. In this case, the next token is an unterminated string and we return this as not as a last property.

**Fix**: When the next token is an untermiated string literal skip it and check for next token.

data.title: Leaving a right-click menu open for about 30 seconds causes a This Window Is No Longer Responding error
data.body:
- VSCode Version: 1.1.1
- OS Version: Windows 10 Build 14342

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Right-click in the editor or sidebar to open the context menu
2. Wait about 30 seconds
3. The "The window is no longer responding, You can reopen or close the window or keep waiting" error message appears. 
4. Clicking "Keep Waiting" allows the program to keep working normally.
